Mimikatz help to dump credintials from memory it is known dumping from lsass 
to detect mimicatz with file creation 

using this rule

<RuleGroup name="" groupRelation="or">
	<FileCreate onmatch="include">
		<TargetFileName condition="contains">mimikatz</TargetFileName>
	</FileCreate>
</RuleGroup>

or bu hunting abnormal lsass.exe behavior 
if the lsass access by other than scvhost.exe that consider sus 
<RuleGroup name="" groupRelation="or">
	<ProcessAccess onmatch="include">
	       <TargetImage condition="image">lsass.exe</TargetImage>
	</ProcessAccess>
</RuleGroup>

using this rules help us  to avoid laot of scvhost 
<RuleGroup name="" groupRelation="or">
	<ProcessAccess onmatch="exclude">
		<SourceImage condition="image">svchost.exe</SourceImage>
	</ProcessAccess>
	<ProcessAccess onmatch="include">
		<TargetImage condition="image">lsass.exe</TargetImage>
	</ProcessAccess>
</RuleGroup>



bu suing power shell to detect mimikatz
Get-WinEvent -Path <Path to Log> -FilterXPath '*/System/EventID=10 and */EventData/Data[@Name="TargetImage"] and */EventData/Data="C:\Windows\system32\lsass.exe"'
